						               													<description>Shooting Bang is a camp party shootout game. Find ways to cooperate with your teammates, defeat all enemies, and become the last surviving player to win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The core mechanism of the game is one card with three uses. The number of cards in hand represents life, the number of cards in hand represents position, and the card in hand represents action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round, the player chooses one of the following actions to execute&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Action: Play a card in hand to activate the effect&amp;#10;     Escape: discard one and draw one or discard two and draw two&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Snipe by guessing the opponent's number by playing attack cards. Those who are hit need to discard the specified number of cards. After a successful hit, the attacker can draw a card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the central deck (eight cards) is exhausted, a card will be randomly drawn from the remaining deck, which means that this number does not exist in the next game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Remove all cards from your opponent's hand to win&amp;#10;There are 18 different weapons and 8 terrain expansions in the game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
